2.21.4

Mistakes in the code:

  • a: v0 is not preserved on call. And for jr, it should followed by $ra if we wish to use a return address.
  • b: v0 is not preserved on call, regristers start with $a should not be used as temporaries.

a. 

  /*Let a represet $a0, b represent $a1, c represent $a2 */

      /*Let the address of a+b corresponds to subfunc_a(),
       that of a-b corresponds to subfunc_b()*/

2.31

2.31

2.31.1

2.31.1(2)

To solve this kind of problem, please follow the following steps.

  • First: Identify the size in the corresponding data segment (begin from 0x1000 0000) and text segment (begin from 0x0040 0000)
  • Second: Identify the corresponding dependency.
  • Third: Judge the correct address.

2.31.1(3)

a. 

  A: lbu $a0, 8000($gp)
     jal 0x0040 0140
  B: sw  $a1, 8040($gp)
     jal 0x0040 0000

b. 

  A: lui $at, 8000($gp)
     ori $a0, $at, 8000($g0)
     jr 0x0040 02C4
  B: sw $a0, 8040($gp)
     j 0x0040 02C0
     (0x0040 02C0:) jal 0x40 0000

2.31.2

The limitation shall be the size of data segment/ text segment in memory. Namely, the size of all data shall not exceed 0x8000, and the size of all instructions shall not exceed
